animal.name: Oberon / Nymphadora
animal.description:
Oberon and Nymphadora are a 6-month old kitten duo looking for their forever home together. Nymphadora is shy and loving and Oberon is playful. 

Nymphadora is an adorable tabby girl who is sweet and very affectionate once she gets to know you. She might start out shy but will warm up with encouragement. She loves to be scratched above her tail.

Once she feels comfortable, this pretty lady loves to explore her environment and eat any lickable treats like Churus! Her favorite toys are made of soft rabbit fur, which she likes to carry in her mouth. Nymphadora is a medium-energy cat. She likes to play but also needs time to be calm and observe those around her.

This little beauty is reserved and may need some coaxing and plenty of space to feel brave enough to seek affection from her humans. She will need to go home with her bonded brother Oberon, who will help her relax into the cozy indoor life. 

Oberon is a cute white-and-tabby boy who loves to play. Everything becomes a toy in his paws! His favorite toys are plastic and make clicking noises on hard floors. He also loves feather toys on strings. Oberon is high energy and requires lots of play and exercise. This athletic boy plays well by himself but also enjoys chasing after toys on strings with his humans.

These two sweetie pies currently live in a house with two humans and nine other cats, including their siblings and momma cat. Because Nymphadora is still reserved, she would do best in a quiet home with lots of places to hide, where she can get accustomed to her new environment. She would prefer patient owners who will respect her space while giving her lots of quiet affection. Oberon would also appreciate having owners who enjoy playing with him daily, and where there is perhaps another cat or two (besides Nymphadora) for him to wrestle with. He is also very affectionate and loves to cuddle with other cats and humans on the bed at night. They get along well with other cats and gentle, older children; they haven&#39;t met any dogs yet. 

If you&#39;d like to add double the fun to your home, please consider adding Nymphadora and Oberon to your family.

Three Little Pitties Rescue is a nonprofit dog and cat rescue that partners with the community to make a difference. Our mission is to reduce the homeless pet population through community outreach, free spay and neuter services, and saving all breeds of dogs and cats from the streets or animal shelters that oftentimes have no other option but to euthanize animals for space. This kitty youve found online is lucky to be in our program, and even luckier to have you notice it!

Three Little Pitties Rescue (3LP) wants to set you and your new family member up for success! In addition to a fully vetted furbaby you also receive other additional perks such as a code for a free bag of cat litter AND a code for 50% off a 2nd bag of litter from Catalyst Pet, coupons for a fun visit to Petco, and support through our Facebook Adopters group where you can connect with thousands of other adopters, 3LP volunteers, fosters and staff. We seek to adopt to families who understand that these are rescues and will require continued efforts but are well on their way to being the best kitties that they can be! We ask that you give them time (can take weeks to months) to decompress in their new home, do slow introductions to other pets and let their true personalities have a chance to come through. 

We celebrated our 6 year anniversary this year! Through the combined efforts of all of our hardworking staff and volunteers, we have placed over 14,000 very lucky dogs and cats into amazing homes! By adopting from us, you save TWO lives! The pet you adopt, and you create an opportunity for another animal to be saved in that spot. Together, we can be heroes.

animal.description:
Meet Otto – The Fluffiest, Fiercest, Funniest Kitten Around (Now With a Side of Specialness)!

At just 6 months old, Otto is already a professional floof and an aspiring household ruler. With his long, luxurious fur and intense gaze, he looks like a miniature lion—but don’t worry, he’s more into dramatic stares than actual roars.

Otto specializes in:
   •   The Art of the Pounce – Your toes? Fair game. That random dust bunny? Conquered.
   •   Expert-level Fluff Maintenance – His magnificent mane is a masterpiece, and he knows it.
   •   Master of Hide-and-Seek – Think he’s napping in one spot? Think again—he’s vanished like a fluffy ninja.

Now, here’s the part that makes Otto even more unique: Otto has tested positive for FeLV (Feline Leukemia Virus). It’s a virus that only affects cats—not people or other animals—and it just means Otto needs a little extra consideration. He must either be the only cat in the home or live with other FeLV-positive felines. While FeLV can be spread through close contact with other cats, Otto can live a happy, love-filled life—especially in a calm, indoor-only environment with regular vet care and lots of playtime.

FeLV-positive cats like Otto often get overlooked, but they deserve the same love, cozy laps, and forever homes as any other cat. In fact, Otto’s zest for life and goofy energy prove that he’s not letting anything slow him down.

Are you ready for Otto’s adorable antics, fluffy dominance, and heart of gold? Apply to adopt this handsome little mischief-maker and give a very special kitten the loving home he deserves!

animal.name: Ash
animal.description:
Ash: Your Chatty, Playful, Slightly Extra New Best Friend! 

Hey there, future human! I&#39;m Ash, and I&#39;m here to bring excitement, entertainment, and just the right amount of chaos into your life. If you&#39;re looking for a cat with a BIG personality and a love for the spotlight, congrats--you found me!

Why I&#39;m Awesome:
/ Very friendly - I love people and will absolutely be involved in whatever you&#39;re doing.
/ Super chatty - Got a story to tell? Great! I&#39;ll tell you one right back.
/ Litter trained - Because manners matter.
/ Playtime champion - Wand toys? Yes. Zoomies? Oh, absolutely.
/ Fashion-forward - I actually enjoy playing dress-up. Yes, I&#39;m that fabulous.
/ Professional bed-making supervisor - If you don&#39;t have cat fur tucked into your sheets, did you even make the bed?
/ Dog-friendly - With slow introductions, I could totally be besties with a respectful pup!
/ Kid-friendly - I don&#39;t mind tiny humans, especially if they know how to play or cuddle!
/ Cuddling Expert - I love a good cuddle session! Carry me around while you work on things? Absolutely! Put me in a baby sling so you can go hands-free? 10/10!

A Few Quirks:
 Other cats? Eh, let&#39;s just say I require slow introductions. I have a BIG personality, and not every cat can handle all this greatness.
 Furniture beware - If you don&#39;t have enough scratching posts, your couch might become my new project. Solution? Get me ALL the scratching posts!

So, are you ready to share your home with a playful, talkative, and slightly dramatic best friend? Fill out an adoption application today, and let&#39;s start our adventure together! 
If you are interested in learning more or would like to set up a meet-and-greet please fill out an adoption application on our website: www.hsbcpets.com/adopt

animal.name: Raccoon
animal.description:
Despite his name, you would never find this kitty in the trash! Raccoon loves the cushy comfy indoor cat life despite him growing up with little to no human interaction as an outdoor roaming kitten. Raccoon is usually draped on some kind of furniture that has soft comfy bedding and/or a nice sunny spot to sleep in. His big round tummy is proof of his exceptional appetite and how he typically chooses to spend his day. Doing nothing.

Raccoon came into the rescue a surrender from a volunteer who was going to rehome them herself when we offered to help. She had been trapping and neutering cats in her area to help reduce the numbers of roaming intact cats. Raccoon was a kitten when he first got to be an &#34;indoor&#34; cat so he was quite under socialized. He&#39;s come a long ways to opting in to being petted and handled. He still doesn&#39;t always trust it, but once you get him going, he melts pretty quickly. Trust is slow to build with him, but it does build the more times we work with him.

Raccoon gets along with other cats and kittens, but he usually doesn&#39;t choose to interact with them since that would infringe on his lazy nap time. No one disturbs him, and he doesn&#39;t disturb anyone else. He doesn&#39;t seem particularly attached to his sister, Little Peach, either. He doesn&#39;t mind dogs, but boisterous ones do scare him a bit. As long as he has a way to escape and the dogs have or learn to have manners, he could live in a home with dogs. Raccoon could also live with kids as long as they don&#39;t chase or grab at him and learn how to respect him.
